Colombia May Cut Gasoline Costs by End of Month, Caracol Reports

-- B y   H e a t h e r   W a l s h
-- 
2011-08-22T14:14:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/colombia-may-cut-gasoline-costs-by-end-of-month-caracol-reports.html
Colombian Mining Minister Carlos Rodado said the government may reduce the price of gasoline by
as much as 2 percent at the end of this month, Bogota-based
broadcaster  Radio Caracol  reported.  Rodado will meet today with Finance Minister Juan Carlos Echeverry to discuss the reduction in government-set fuel
prices, Caracol said today on its website after interviewing
Rodado.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Heather Walsh at 
 hlwalsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
